title: Lake Farm Roman fort
description: Large Roman military installation near present-day Wimborne Minster in Dorset. It was established very shortly after Claudian invasion (ca. 44 CE), and later served as a vexillation fortress.

properties.title: OSM location of Lake Farm Roman fort

properties.description: Representative point location marking the modern location of Lake Farm, based on OpenStreetMap. According to published reports, the remains of the fort were excavated 240 meters north of Lake Farm.
properties.title: OSM location of modern Lake Farm
